The paper deals with deep learning and convolutional neural networks, which are primarily studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of depthwise separable convolutions is a novel technique that falls under the category of neural architecture search (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also deals with image classification, which is a common task in natural language processing (cs.CL) as well.
